    "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Persist the Sony PSK into generated add-on settings**\n\nWhen a Sony Bravia user enters the PSK here and the Step 5 switch test succeeds, the value is only saved as `tvSonyPsk`; `wizardStateToAddonSettings()` emits the Sony HDMI ports but never writes `sony_psk`, while the add-on's Sony backend requires that setting before switching. That means the configurator can validate the switch during setup, then deploy a config where `tv_switching_enabled` is true but runtime handoff fails with a missing PSK.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
